2022-06-06','2022-06-06','SN Puram ward 21','To spread the message of ecological  restoration and environmental conservaton in the young thoughts.','<p>The children from Veycode Government L.P. school were joined the ecorestoration site along with the women groups for planting seedlings in the coastal region of Kodungallur. The programme was inaugurated by E T. Tyson Master, MLA, Kaipamangalam.</p>','2','23',NULL,NULL,'SN Puram','21','17','25','programs','Recent','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 06:48:14',1,1,0,10,13,0,0,0,1,5,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685688658.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(183,127,'Coastal Restoration Seed bed & Threatened species nursery','2022-06-08','2022-06-08','MES Asmabi College','1. To promote the message of  local gene pool\n2. Development of threatened species nursery  increase the survival rates and Seed beds are protected environment which can maintain the seeds in good physical conditions \n    and also can optimize their germination.','<p>In connection with MAD week event, Bhoomithrasena Club of MES Asmabi College have gathered to develop seed bed for coastal restoration on 8th June 2022. The seeds collected from the local area especially the <em>Calophyllum inophyllum</em> were sowed in the seed bed for its germination with proper spacing and nutrient support.</p>','2','38',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12','35','programs','Cell','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 08:54:34',1,1,0,9,29,0,NULL,2,1,7,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685692897.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(184,127,'Coastal Vegetation belt Nursery','2022-06-09','2022-06-09','SN Puram ward 1,19,20,21','To promote the message of local gene pool by the engagement of women in MNREGA scheme','<p>The Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation and SN puram grama panchayath engaged the women especially in the MNREGA scheme for the ecorestoration processes of disaster hit coastal zones. In this MAD week, to promote the message of the local gene pool they developed a nursery by collecting the seeds and seedlings from their local area and that were kept for restoration sites this year.</p>','2','40',NULL,NULL,'SN Puram','1,19,20,21','15','43','programs','Cell','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 16:58:26',1,1,0,11,29,0,0,3,1,8,'3','8',NULL,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685694194.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(185,127,'Nursery for threatened rain forest tree species restoration','2022-06-10','2022-06-10','MES Asmabi College','1.To develop threatened species gene pool\n2.Use the germinated species for restoration based on niche profiling and niche modelling.','<p>The Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation and Research Department of Botany at MES Asmabi College officially inaugurated the seed germination centre for threatened tree species. Seedlings of nine threatened (IUCN) tree species were successfully germinated this year to use in the identified restoration sites based on niche profiling and niche modelling. In collaboration with forest department and local community the restoration processes will be taken place. The rain forest tree species such as <em>Diospyros crumenata, Prioria pinnata, Hopea ponga, Hopea parviflora</em>, <em>Baccaurea courtallensis, Humboldtia vahliana, Aporosa bourdillonii, Syzygium occidentale </em>were produced more in number.</p>','2','52',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'14','51','Other','Cell','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 16:56:49',1,1,0,9,43,0,0,2,1,7,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Experiancial',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685695853.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(186,127,'Releasing new edition of Forest Rights Act 2006 book','2022-10-08','2022-10-08','Online platform','Publication of new edition of the book on Forest Right Act 2006','<p>&nbsp;The modified third edition of our book on Forest Right Act 2006, which entitled &ldquo;Forest Resource Right and Tribal Development &ndash; One and half decade of Forest Rights Act 2006 in Kerala&rdquo; . The book was released through an online event. The book deals with a critical review of the FRA implementation in Kerala and scope in preservation and non alienation of forest and tribal land in Kerala. The book was coauthored three board members of the Hornbill Foundation, Dr. K.H. Amitha Bachan, Who is a member of FRA 200g committee on PVTG rights, Ministry of Tribal Affairs (MoTA), Govt. of India, Dr. Maya Mohan, Sociologist and faculty of Christ University Banglore, Dr. Divya Kalathingal, FRA expert completed PhD from Tata Institute of Social Science(TISS), Mumbai, working as faculty in the Sankrit University, Tirur Campus, Malappuram, Kerala.</p>','6','25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'63','42','programs','Cell','6,7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 16:55:05',5,1,0,8,17,0,0,1,1,2,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685697193.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(188,127,'Anniversary Celebration of Coastal Ecorestoration at SN Puram Grama Panchayath','2022-08-30','2022-08-30','MES Asmabi College','To celebrate the anniversary  of  Coastal Eco-restoration','<p>The success of our one year coastal restoration process in the four wards of Sree Narayanapuram Grama Panchayath was celebrated on 30th August 2022.The annual conference of the project and the inauguration of the second phase of the project was inaugurated by P.K. Devis Master (President, District Panchayath, Thrissur) at MES Asmabi College. Panchayath President Mr. M.S. Mohanan presided over the function and Dr. A. Biju, Principal MES Asmabi College was the chief guest.Dr. Amitha Bachan, who is leading the project, gave a detailed presentation of the one-year operation of the project.</p>','2','23',NULL,NULL,'SN Puram',NULL,'16','48','programs','Cell','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 16:54:00',1,1,0,5,18,0,0,2,1,3,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Marginalised',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685957657.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(189,127,'Meeting at SN Puram Grama panchayath','2022-12-02','2022-12-02','SN Puram Gramapanchayath Office','Conducted for the discussion of existing activities','<p>A meeting was conducted at Sree Narayanapuram Grama Panchayath for the discussion of existing activities regarding the restoration practices and new proposals.</p>','1','1',NULL,NULL,'SN Puram',NULL,'3','5','programs','Cell','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 16:53:10',1,0,0,0,1,0,0,0,0,0,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Other',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1685700011.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(191,127,'Niche Specific Restoration of Sacred Grove at Thalikulam, Thrissur','2022-11-08','2022-11-08','Thalikulam','1. To plant the sapling of a low elevation threatened tree species \n2.To give awareness about need for niche specific ecological restoration practices','<p>Sree Narayana College, Nattika in collaboration with Hornbill Foundation organized ecorestoration of sacred grove at Thalikulam. The programme was inaugurated by the chief guest Mr. Febin Francis (Thrissur district coordinator, Kerala State Biodiversity Board) by planting the sapling of a low elevation threatened tree species in auspicious prescence of Dr. K.H. Amitha Bachan and Ms. Devika M Anilkumar. Teachers and students of Department of Botany, Sree Narayana College, Nattika planted the remaining saplings in the sacred grove and take over the session. A total of 15 saplings were planted. The planted threatened saplings include <em>Prioria pinnata</em> (Kulavu), <em>Hopea ponga</em> (Thambakam) and <em>Diospyros crumenata</em> (Karimaram) along with their associates species which occupies the same niche.</p>','8','44',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'16','38','programs','Cell','7,8',NULL,'2023-06-02 16:52:29',3,5,0,12,32,0,0,1,1,6,'3','8','127'