ue biodiversity found in Northeast India, particularly highlighting the diversity of wild banana species.</p>\n\n<p>All the students listened carefully the lectures delivered by the invited guests and they interacted well with the students. Thus the programme was a grant success. It was successful in promoting awareness about biodiversity and its conservation. The talks delivered by Dr. Joby Paul and Dr. Alfred Joe provided valuable insights and enhanced the understanding of the participants. The event not only highlighted the importance of environmental conservation but also showcased the dedication of the college towards creating a sustainable future.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, the Environment Day Programme was a significant step towards fostering environmental consciousness among students and encouraging them to actively participate in biodiversity conservation efforts.</p>','8','76',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Seminar','Cell','7',NULL,'2023-09-22 14:19:50',3,5,0,12,64,0,0,11,2,58,'77','8','613',NULL,1,61,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695392411.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(234,145,'Karkkidakamaasacharanam','2023-08-08','2023-08-08','Botany lab','Karkkidakamaasacharam','<p>PG &amp; Research Dept. of Botany conducted various programmes as a part of &lsquo;karkkidakamaasacharam 2023&rsquo; on 8th August 2023. On 8th August, students prepared &lsquo;karkkidakakanji&rsquo; and served the same to the staff of college and to the students. Principal inaugurated the function. An exhibition of &lsquo;Dhaspushpam&rsquo; and various edible leaves which were commonly used in houses were also conducted.</p>','94','78',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Other','Cell','7',NULL,'2023-09-22 14:28:10',19,75,0,12,66,0,0,11,2,0,'8','8','601',NULL,1,61,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(235,145,'Ozone Day Celebration 2023','2023-09-15','2023-09-15','SEMINAR HALL','Ozone layer protection awareness to students','<p>As part of World Ozone Day 2023, Department of Botany, Science Forum and Bhoomitrasena Club of MES Asmabi College organized a power point presentation competition for college students on 15-9-2023 based on the focal theme of world ozone day 2023. Several students participated in the competition and from the participants two presented the PPT well. Thus two students from the Botany department shared the first prize. The students who got first prize are Naswif KM, III BSc Botany and Amna, I BSc Botany. Shaheedha T.M., Assistant Professsor of Botany distributed cash price to students.</p>','8','50',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Competition','Recent','7',NULL,'2023-09-22 14:33:10',3,5,0,8,42,0,0,7,1,0,'6','8','613',NULL,1,36,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(236,127,'Nature, Society and Sustainability: Changing Contours - Golden Jubilee Conference (MESAC-19): 19th – 20th March 2019','2019-03-19','2019-03-20','MES Asmabi College','A two day National conference was organized by MES Asmabi College, Kodungallur on behalf of Golden Jubilee celebration supported by Kerala State Biodiversity Board and Kerala State Higher Education Council. The conference was conducted as part of UNANP and became the last programme of the academic year 2018-2019.','<p>Two days National conference was organized by MES Asmabi College, Kodungallur behalf of Golden Jubilee celebration supported by Kerala State Biodiversity Board and Kerala State Higher Education Council and Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation. The conference was conducted as the part of UNANP and became the last programme of academic year 2018-2019. The conference officially inaugurated by Dr. V Balakrishnan, Member Secretary of Kerala State Biodiversity Board. Dr. S. Faizi delivered the plenary talk who is a renowned Indian ecologist specializing in Biodiversity Management and International Environmental Policy. He started career as Field Biologist. Headed an international environmental NGO, has been UNESCO Fellow, Consultant Ecologist to IUCN and also a Biodiversity Expert. The inauguration section is followed by a plenary talk by Dr. A Ramakrishna. He is a Zoologist and also specialized in Taxonomy and Environmental conservation. He has 36 years of Research Experience. Dr. Sulthan Ahmed Ismailis an Indian soil biologist and ecologist. His work has centered on techniques for recycling biodegradable waste into fertilizer using local varieties of earthworms and on soil bioremediation, who coined the term Vermitech in 1992. A total of 231 students and 35 teachers participated in the programme.</p>','35','231',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Conference','Cell','7,14',NULL,'2023-09-25 14:48:07',5,30,0,101,130,0,0,10,3,33,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695653332.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(237,127,'3 Days National workshop on Research data analysis Application of GIS and Research writing in Ecology Environment Conservation biology and Angiosperm Taxonomy – 23rd to 25th October 2019','2019-10-23','2019-10-25','MES Asmabi College','Training on Ecology Environment Conservation biology and Angiosperm Taxonomy Research data analysis Application of GIS Research writing','<p>The training on Ecology Environment Conservation biology and Angiosperm Taxonomy in the fields 1. Research data analysis, 2. Application of GIS and 3. Research writing was inaugurated by Dr. N Sasidharan, Scientist, KFRI. The workshop was conducted in three days based on research data analysis and application of GIS in research writing. The programme had both theoretical and technical sessions in the areas of life science, forestry, conservation biology, environmental science and social science. The technical session was handled by Dr. N. Sasidharan on Advancements of Angiosperm Taxonomy, Ms. Aswini, CGIST on Fundamental of GIS and its application in Ecology and Conservation, Dr. Amitha Bachan K.H., Tropical Vegetation Dynamics. A total of 21 students and niche teachers were participated in the training. The workshop was a great success and well supported the students, researchers and professionals in the interdisciplinary expertise in conservation and environment science.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','9','21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Workshop','Cell','4,14',NULL,'2023-09-25 14:52:32',3,6,0,7,14,0,0,3,1,12,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695653578.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(239,127,'National Conference on Democracy, Land and Resource management Rights of Adivasis and Challenges of strengthening Adivasi Grama Sabha in Kerala – 18th and 19th December 2019','2019-12-18','2019-12-19','MES Asmabi College','A session in the CFR conference to discuss the IPR provision in the Forest Right Act 2006','<p>A National Conference on Democracy, Land and Resource management Rights of Adivasis was conducted from 18th &ndash; 19th December 2019 by Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation in collaboration with MES Asmabi College. The programme envisages to bring out the challenges faced by the Adivasi Grama Sabha in Kerala for their empowerment and also to meet their rights. More than 50 Adivasis from different communities such as Kadar, Kattunaika, Kurumba, Paniya Cholanaika etc participated in the programme. The session was chaired by C.R Bijoy, the papers were presented by Adv. Jessin Irena, Adv. Preetha. The participated 30 Adivasi students had an opportunity to enroll in the certificate course offered based on the conservation, sustainability and indigenous rights.</p>','22','69',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Conference','Recent','7',NULL,'2023-09-23 07:29:54',10,12,0,20,49,0,0,11,9,17,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695653756.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(240,127,'International Webinar on Conservation and Right debate series – 10th – 20th October 2020','2020-10-10','2020-10-20','Online Zoom platform','Conduct series of talks on conservation and right','<p>In this era of climate change and pandemic, it has been proved that the resource conservation practices of indigenous people are very vital. This conservation and right debate series brings up discourses on historical and contemporary understanding of conservation and how it interacts with the right question. The webinar brought out the discussions from several disciplines with the eminent resource persons C.R.Bijoy, Madhu Sarin, Pramod G Krishnan, Dr. S. Faizi, Dr. Aparna Watve, Mrs. Poorva S Joshi, Adv. Shomona Khanna and Dr. Amitha Bachan KH. They talked about the historical and conceptual perspective of conservation, social justice and law, sustainability, implementation of FRA in neoliberal developmental space. Nearly 100 participants in each day were attended the webinar with fruitful discussion.</p>','20','320',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Webinar','Recent','1',NULL,'2023-09-23 09:31:12',12,8,0,140,180,0,0,56,2,170,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695653940.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(241,127,'The Riparian Forest for Fish, Rivers and People” on May 21st “The world fish migration day: 21st May 2022','2022-05-21','2022-05-21','Online','International Conference on : The Riparian Forest for Fish, Rivers and People” \nCelebration of \"The world fish migration day”\nThe programme envisages to bring out a status document on riparian zones of various rivers of Kerala in November 2022 towards the concept of “ecological management of rivers” in an international workshop. A comprehensive status on Chalakkudy River and riparian ecorestoration protocol will be used as a baseline.','<p>As part of the Celebration of &quot;The world fish migration day&rdquo; an International Conference on &ldquo;The Riparian Forest for Fish, Rivers and People&rdquo; was organized. The programme envisages to bring out a status document on riparian zones of various rivers of Kerala in November 2022 towards the concept of &ldquo;ecological management of rivers&rdquo; in an international workshop. A comprehensive status on Chalakkudy River and riparian ecorestoration protocol will be used as a baseline. The Centre for Ecology, Taxonomy, Conservation and Climate change (CEtC) of Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation (WGHF) at Research Department of Botany MES Asmabi College campus organised an online event &ldquo;The Riparian Forest for Fish, Rivers and People&rdquo; on May 21st &ldquo;The world fish migration day&rdquo;. This event is joining hands with other events happened across the world linked with &lsquo;World Fish Migration Day &ldquo;on the 21st May 2022. This is to propagate the requisite of &ldquo;Ecological Restoration and management of the Riparian forests across the Western Ghats&rdquo;. Various scientists, researchers, local people and community organisations presented their views on various rivers across Kerala part of Western Ghats. The event was in collaboration with the Department of Aquatic Biology and Fisheries, University of Kerala, Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation, CEtC &amp; Research Department of Botany MES Asmabi College, Fish Migration Foundation, Society for Ecorestoration (SER). A total of 62 students participated in the programme.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2','62',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'48','72','Conference','Recent','7,8',NULL,'2023-09-23 09:42:43',1,1,0,24,38,0,0,12,3,0,'3','8','127',NULL,1,12,'River Dependent Communities Across South India, Scientists, Research Fellows',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Marginalised',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695654249.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(242,127,'Training for Officials and Tribal GS member Forest Right Act and Community Forest Resource in Kerala Towards Policy Advocacy: 28th September 2021','2021-09-28','2021-09-28','Online','1. Develop a Policy advocacy note on the performance of the implementation of CFR in Kerala and its Challenges to Govt of Kerala. \n2. Present and discuss the National and Kerala scenario with the community in Kerala\n3. Empowerment of the Tribal Grama Sabha members in Kerala','<p>The major agendas of the programme were (i) To develop a Policy advocacy note on the performance of the implementation of CFR in Kerala and its Challenges to Govt of Kerala. (ii) Present and discuss the National and Kerala scenario with the community in Kerala (iii) Empowerment of the Tribal Grama Sabha members in Kerala. The program was organized by the Tata Institute of Social Science (TISS), Mumbai, in collaboration with the Centre for Tribal and Natural History Studies (TNHS) of Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation at the Research Department of Botany, MES Asmabi College. The program was to get opinions and develop a Policy and Advocacy Note to the Government of Kerala as per their request to TISS, Mumbai. Dr. Geethanjoy Sahu, Assistant Professor, Centre for Science, Technology and Society, TISS made the Keynote, and Dr. Amitha Bachan KH, Assistant Professor, CEtC WGHF; Research Department of Botany MES Asmabi College made the plenary talk. Nearly 21 students and three teachers were part of the programme.</p>','3','21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'94','0','Webinar','Cell','6,7',NULL,'2023-09-25 15:04:43',2,1,0,7,14,0,0,2,19,1,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,'Tribal Grama Sabha Members Across Kerala',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Marginalised',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695654295.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(243,127,'Coastal Ecorestoration Phase 1 Inauguration','2021-09-16','2021-09-16','Coastal Beach P Vemballur','1. Ianugration of the First Phase of the Coastal Ecorestoration programm by Mr. Saji Cheriyan, Hon Minster of Fisheres and Cultural Affairs, Kerala.\n\n2. Declaration of  the Successful implementation of Phase 1. Ecorestoration of the Arappthodu, streams draining to sea involving MGNREGA','<p>The major agenda of the programme was 1. Inauguration of the First Phase of the Coastal Ecorestoration programme by Mr. Saji Cheriyan, Hon Minster of Fisheries and Cultural Affairs, Kerala. 2. Declaration of the Successful implementation of Phase 3. Ecorestoration of the Arappthodu, streams draining to sea involving MGNREGA. The Program was inaugurated by Mr. Saji Cheriyan, Hon. Minister of Fisheries and Cultural Affairs, Govt. of Kerala in the venue arranged at the Coastal Ward- 1 of the SN Puram Grama Panchayath near Vekkod beach. Mr. Tyson Master, MLA chaired the function in the auspicious presence of Mr. Devis Master, President of District Panchayath, Mrs. Girija, President, of District Panchayath, Mr. M S. Mohanan, President Grama Panchayath. Dr. Amitha Bachan K H, Assistant Professor and Director of the Research Extension Centre (CEtC) of WGHF, MES Asmabi College presented the project details. All the representatives of the Panchayath and local community members gathered. The minister declared the project as a unique one for the scientific and people involved ecorestoration program to save the coastal belt. A total of 24 students and two teachers were participated in the programme.</p>','2','24',NULL,NULL,'SN Puram','1, 21','24','42','Refreshing','Recent','6,7,8',NULL,'2023-09-23 09:58:18',1,1,0,6,18,0,0,3,1,14,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,'Coastal Women','Women working MGNREGA',NULL,NULL,'Marginalised',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695654468.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(244,127,'One day workshop on ecorestoration 30.03.2021','2021-03-30','2021-03-30','MES Asmabi College','To provide awareness on coastal ecorestoration and management by involving the local community','<p>To provide awareness on coastal ecorestoration and management by involving the local community was the major agenda of the programme. A sensitisation workshop was conducted after developing a draft profile of the ecosystem and biodiversity in the SN puram Grama Panchayat. The workshop was held at the MES Asmabi college on 30th March 2021. The workshop was inaugurated by Dr Asma V M, Head of the Department of Botany, in the auspicious presence of Shri. M.S. Mohanan, President SN puram Grama Panchayat. Dr. Martin Gopurathingal, Dr. KH Amitha Bachan and Adv. Alphonsa Jojan of Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation was the resource person. Sixty participants including BMC members, farmers, members of the Kizhakootu trust other interested persons from the Panchayats, selected research fellows from different colleges around the area and local women were the participants.</p>','4','42',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0','0','Workshop','Recent','4,6,7',NULL,'2023-09-23 10:04:35',1,3,0,17,25,0,0,3,1,9,'3','8','127',NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cell','1695654571.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3',NULL,NULL),(245,127,'Plant Count at Coastal Ecorestoration site: 5th June 2023','2023-06-05','2023-06-05','19, 21 -  Wards of Sreenarayan Puram, Kodungallur','Ensure the survival rate and the status of restoration in the disaster hit coastal zones of the Panchayath.','<p>As part of the World Environment Day 2023, BMC, Sree Narayana Puram Grama Panchayath and CEtC Western Ghats Hornbill Foundation jointly conducted a plant count at coastal vegetation belt restoration at 19 and 21 ward of the panchayath. The programme was inaugurated by Shri. M.S. Mohanan, president, SN Puram Grama Panchayath by planting a sapling. Students from Biodiversity Clubs of various schools participated in the programme. The women from MGNREA and the students together counted the number of saplings to ensure its survival rate and the status of restoration in the disaster hit coastal zones of the Panchayath.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','5','29',NULL,NULL,NULL,'19, 21','14','28','Workshop','Recent','1,6,7,8',NULL,'